{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make St George\u2019s Day a national bank holiday in England every year",
        "additional_details": "England has fewer bank holidays than Scotland and Northern Ireland, which recognise St Andrew\u2019s Day and St Patrick\u2019s Day. Creating a St George\u2019s Day holiday would bring England in line with the rest of the UK, celebrate national identity and culture, and support tourism, community events and local economies. It would also help address the UK\u2019s relatively low number of public holidays compared to many European countries.",
        "background": "Make St George\u2019s Day (23 April) a national bank holiday in England each year, recognising England\u2019s patron saint and bringing England in line with other UK nations that already have national day public holidays.",
